<title>MAME arcade machines</title>
<category>vidgames</category>
<via href='http://www.codinghorror.com/blog'>Coding Horror</via>
<body>
<p>I've heard of <a href='http://www.mame.net'>MAME</a>, the arcade video game emulation software.
I hadn't known that there's an entire cottage industry springing up to provide arcade-style enclosures
for computers running MAME:
<a href='http://www.slikstik.com'>SlikStik</a>,
<a href='http://www.dreamauthentics.com'>DreamAuthentics</a>,
<a href='http://www.mameroom.com'>MAMEroom</a>, and
<a href='http://www.dreamarcades.com/'>Dream Arcades</a>, to name a few businesses.
You can even get <a href='http://www.arcadetokens.com/html/mame_tokens.html'>MAME-branded arcade tokens</a>!
</p>
